channel.desc: Alicia Barry presents Australia's leading daily business and finance show, bringing viewers up to date on market moves, economic trends and the forces affecting consumers, investors, employees, and businesses big and small.

channel.title: The World
channel.desc: There's never been a more important time to stay in touch with what's happening in our world. Weeknights at 9pm AEST, Girish Sawlani presents the latest international news from correspondents and interviews with guests.

channel.desc: The latest international news and the day's top stories from a European perspective. Our broadcast partner DW brings you live coverage from Berlin with updated reports and expert analysis on the big global issues and events.

channel.name: ABC News 24 AU
channel.desc: Sarah Ferguson presents Australia's premier daily current affairs program, delivering agenda-setting journalism and interviews that hold the powerful to account. Plus analysis from 7.30's Political Editor Jacob Greber.

channel.name: ABC News 24 AU
channel.title: Landline
channel.desc: A tasty sampler of stories from the land, covering food, agriculture, crops, climate, business and innovation, and meeting the fascinating people who make rural and regional communities unique. Presented by Pip Courtney.

channel.name: ABC News 24 AU
channel.title: The Pacific
channel.desc: Johnson Raela and Alice Lolohea bring you the stories that matter to the region, told by our trusted network of in-country correspondents, with the latest in news, politics, sports and entertainment from across the Pacific.

channel.name: ABC News 24 AU
channel.title: News Breakfast
channel.desc: As the day begins get the facts you need to stay informed. James Glenday and Emma Rebellato bring you the latest news, overnight developments and top stories, joined by Catherine Murphy with sport and Nate Byrne with weather.
